            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/837-12" resp="#ngibson">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc><persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1977">Paul, patriarch of
                                Antioch</persName> extended his ministry to the poor to the banks on
                            all sides of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/586"
                                >Constantinople</placeName> and in the nearby cities of <placeName
                                ref="http://syriaca.org/place/622">Chalcedon</placeName>, <placeName
                                ref="http://syriaca.org/place/502">Nicomedia</placeName>, <placeName
                                ref="http://syriaca.org/place/439">Cyzicus</placeName>, <placeName
                                ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2835">Prusias</placeName>, and
                                <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2790">Heraclea</placeName>,
                            as far as the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/503">sea of
                                Pontus</placeName>. He bought and distributed clothing and bathed
                            the poor and strangers.</desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/poor http://syriaca.org/keyword/alms http://syriaca.org/keyword/care http://syriaca.org/keyword/cities http://syriaca.org/keyword/clothing http://syriaca.org/keyword/washing"/>
